<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[113,765,1502,1951]" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis box="[151,203,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Notes</emphasis>
. – The type specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[451,618,1502,1526]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campanulata">
<emphasis box="[451,618,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Ixia campanulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<collectingRegion box="[709,764,1502,1526]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Cape</collectingRegion>
herbarium in G-PREL. 
<bibRefCitation author="MERRILL" box="[361,584,1535,1559]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" page="327" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" pagination="291 - 375" refId="ref30489" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1938). A critical consideration of Houttuyn's new genera and new species of plants, 1773 - 1783. J. Arnold Arbor. 19: 291 - 375." type="journal article" year="1938">MERRILL (1938: 327)</bibRefCitation>
did not recognise it as Houttuyn’s. 
<bibRefCitation author="BROWN" box="[292,507,1568,1592]" firstAuthor="BROWN" page="133" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" pagination="129 - 137" refId="ref28215" refString="BROWN, N. E. (1929). The Iridaceae of Burman's Florae capensis prodromus. Bull. Misc. Inform. Kew 1929: 129 - 137." type="journal article" year="1929">BROWN (1929: 133)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="LEWIS" box="[560,764,1567,1592]" firstAuthor="LEWIS" page="126" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" pagination="45 - 195" refId="ref30099" refString="LEWIS, G. J. (1962). South African Iridaceae. The genus Ixia. J. S. African Bot. 28: 45 - 195." type="journal article" year="1962">LEWIS (1962: 126)</bibRefCitation>
recognised this collection as the 
<typeStatus box="[445,536,1600,1624]" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">holotype</typeStatus>
, whereas GOLDBLATT &amp; MANNING (2016: 185) correctly accepted Brown’s mention as an implicit lectotypification. Four collections of possibly different gatherings are present in UPS-THUNB for 
<taxonomicName box="[569,689,1699,1722]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis box="[569,689,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Ixia aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(UPS- THUNB n° 917, n° 918, n° 919 and n° 920). The better-preserved specimen is designated here as the 
<typeStatus box="[467,563,1763,1787]" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[113,765,1502,1951]" lastBlockId="23.[801,1452,277,367]" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">
Several other collections of 
<taxonomicName box="[442,484,1797,1820]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,484,1797,1820]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Ixia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. are in Houttuyn’s 
<collectingRegion box="[707,763,1796,1820]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Cape</collectingRegion>
herbarium: 
<taxonomicName box="[238,348,1828,1852]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[238,348,1828,1852]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">I. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (G-PREL [G008181221]), 
<taxonomicName authority="D. Delaroche" authorityName="D. Delaroche" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monadelpha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">I. monadelpha</emphasis>
D. Delaroche
</taxonomicName>
(G-PREL [G008181217, G008181218]), 
<taxonomicName box="[113,249,1894,1918]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polystachya">
<emphasis box="[113,249,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">I. polystachya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (G-PREL [G008181219]), and 
<taxonomicName box="[636,733,1894,1918]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scillaris">
<emphasis box="[636,733,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">I. scillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (G-PREL [G00818120]). Two further specimens identified by Houttuyn as 
<taxonomicName authority="D. Delaroche" authorityName="D. Delaroche" box="[939,1217,277,301]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[939,1071,277,301]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">I. grandiflora</emphasis>
D. Delaroche
</taxonomicName>
are now recognised in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ker Gawl." authorityName="Ker Gawl." box="[801,1003,310,334]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Sparaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[801,887,310,333]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">Sparaxis</emphasis>
Ker Gawl.
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(D. Delaroche) Ker Gawl." authorityName="Ker Gawl." baseAuthorityName="D. Delaroche" box="[1035,1452,310,334]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[1035,1172,310,334]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="178">S. grandiflora</emphasis>
(D. Delaroche) Ker Gawl.
</taxonomicName>
(G-PREL [G00818122, G00818123]).
</paragraph>
